page.title: 11Housing In The Denmead Area.
page.content: Although Denmead, as a village, has existed for many centuries it has only begun to grow very recently. Most of Denmead has been built since 1945, much since 1970, and Denmead is still growing with new housing developments on the south side of the village. Similarly, all of the part of Wecock that falls into our area has been built since 1965. It will not be long before the "Green Belt" between Denmead and Wecock is built upon. Most of the housing in this area is high-class, owner-occupied with 7 rooms or more in each house. With the high rate of construction in Denmead the number of people who have just moved into the area is now up to 11%. No new houses can be built in Wecock as there is no land available that would, at this time, get planning permission.
